        "type": "content",
        "fullWidth": false,
        "centerAlign": true,
        "content": "<p>A really quick tip from me today and something I wanted to share as it&#8217;s so obvious and yet I often forget to do it, hopefully this might help someone else.</p>\n<p><strong>Always</strong> add a full stop to your alt text, it will tell the screenreader to pause when describing your images and provides a much better and more accessible experience.</p>\n"
      }
